### HEALTH FINANCING ###
categories {
  title: "Health Financing"
  description: "Health financing is a key pillar of health systems that can ensure people can access quality health services and have their health needs addressed, without suffering personal financial hardship. But, while total health spending has grown across all income levels over the past 20 years, higher income countries account for the predominant majority of this spending. This means individuals in low income countries often have to pay out of their pockets to cover health expenses, pushing millions into extreme poverty as a result."

  # Total Health Expenditure
  blocks {
    title: "Total Health Expenditure"
    description: "Total health spending refers to health expenditure from all financing sources, including domestic government, external aid, domestic private, and out-of-pocket health spending."
